  "text": "Kubernetes implements API group storage version registration through a multi-layer system coordinating which API versions are used for etcd storage. The system consists of several key components:\n\n## REST Storage Providers\nAll API groups in `pkg/registry/*/rest/storage_*.go` define REST storage providers that implement `NewRESTStorage()` methods. These providers register both v1 and (where applicable) v1beta1 storage versions:\n- **With v1beta1 mapping**: `pkg/registry/admissionregistration/rest/storage_apiserver.go`, `pkg/registry/authentication/rest/storage_authentication.go`, `pkg/registry/resource/rest/storage_resource.go`, and `pkg/registry/storage/rest/storage_storage.go` explicitly define both `v1Storage()` and `v1beta1Storage()` methods\n- **v1 only**: Other storage providers like `pkg/registry/apps/rest/storage_apps.go`, `pkg/registry/batch/rest/storage_batch.go`, `pkg/registry/policy/rest/storage_policy.go`, and `pkg/registry/scheduling/rest/storage_scheduling.go` only define `v1Storage()` methods\n\n## ResourceEncodingConfig Interface\nThe `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/storage/resource_encoding_config.go` file defines the critical ResourceEncodingConfig interface with two key methods:\n1. `StorageEncodingFor(schema.GroupResource)` - Returns which GroupVersion is used to store the resource in etcd\n2. `InMemoryEncodingFor(schema.GroupResource)` - Returns the in-memory representation format\n\nThe `DefaultResourceEncodingConfig` implementation provides the `SetResourceEncoding()` method to explicitly map a GroupResource to a specific storage version. This is where v1beta1 to v1 mappings would be configured.\n\n## Storage Version Manager and Tracking\n`staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storageversion/manager.go` defines the Manager interface for tracking which resources need StorageVersion updates. The `ResourceInfo` struct contains:\n- `GroupResource`: The resource being managed\n- `EncodingVersion`: The version used for etcd storage\n- `DirectlyDecodableVersions`: Versions the converter can handle (including v1beta1 even if not served)\n- `ServedVersions`: Versions actually exposed via the API\n\nThe Manager reconciles storage versions across all API server instances by creating/updating StorageVersion objects in the `internal.apiserver.k8s.io` API group.\n\n## StorageVersion API and Migration Control\n`staging/src/k8s.io/api/apiserverinternal/v1alpha1/types.go` defines the StorageVersion CRD which tracks per-server encoding versions and determines when all servers agree on a common storage version (CommonEncodingVersion field).\n\n`staging/src/k8s.io/api/storagemigration/v1alpha1/types.go` defines StorageVersionMigration resources that coordinate the actual migration of data from one storage version to another when the storage version changes.\n\n## Version Registration Chain\nThe full flow is:\n1. REST Storage Provider (e.g., `pkg/registry/admissionregistration/rest/storage_apiserver.go`) calls both `v1Storage()` and `v1beta1Storage()` to register versions\n2. `DefaultStorageFactory.NewConfig()` in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/storage/storage_factory.go` queries ResourceEncodingConfig via `StorageEncodingFor()` to determine which version is the canonical storage version for etcd\n3. The selected storage version is passed to etcd, while other versions are marked as decodable but not the encoding version\n4. StorageVersion Manager registers these decisions via the StorageVersion CRD\n5. `WithStorageVersionPrecondition()` filter in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/filters/storageversion.go` blocks write operations until all API servers report matching storage versions\n\nThe `MergeResourceEncodingConfigs()` function in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/resourceconfig/helpers.go` merges default ResourceEncodingConfig with specific GroupVersionResource overrides to control which version is used for storage."
}

